---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { baseUrl } from '../../utils/base.ts';
---

<Layout
  title="UOMP - User-Owned Memory Protocol"
  description="A user-sovereign authorization protocol for AI Agent memory access."
  lang="en"
  switchHref={baseUrl}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge">Draft-00</span>
      <h1>Your Memory, Your Authorization</h1>
      <p>
        UOMP (User-Owned Memory Protocol) is a user-sovereign authorization protocol that lets you
        temporarily grant AI Agents access to your personal memory data—scoped by tag or key,
        bound to a session, and automatically revoked when the session ends.
      </p>
      <div class="cta">
        <a href={`${baseUrl}en/spec/`} class="btn btn-primary">Read the Spec</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/0xaicrypto/uomp" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-secondary">GitHub Discussions</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why UOMP?</h2>
      <p>
        Today's AI Agents need access to vast amounts of personal data to provide personalized
        service. Existing solutions usually require users to upload data to third-party servers,
        which means users lose direct control, Agents may retain data indefinitely, and access is
        hard to audit.
      </p>
      <p>
        UOMP changes this: your memory stays on your device, and Agents only receive temporary,
        minimal, auditable access.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Core Principles</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🔒</div>
          <h3>User Sovereignty</h3>
          <p>You always own and control your memory data. It never moves to an Agent provider.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🎯</div>
          <h3>Least Privilege</h3>
          <p>Authorize by tag or exact key. Unauthorized data is inaccessible by default.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">⏱️</div>
          <h3>Session Isolation</h3>
          <p>Each grant is bound to an independent session. Access ends when the session ends.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">📋</div>
          <h3>Auditable</h3>
          <p>Every access is logged so you can see exactly what each Agent read or wrote.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <div class="diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 720 260" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="UOMP workflow diagram">
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrowhead-en" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="9" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
              <polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="#22d3ee" />
            </marker>
          </defs>
          <rect x="260" y="20" width="440" height="220" rx="12" fill="#12121a" stroke="#2a2a3a" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="480" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="12" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">User Host</text>

          <rect x="20" y="100" width="110" height="60" rx="8" fill="#0a0a0f" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="75" y="135" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">Agent</text>

          <rect x="300" y="60" width="120" height="44" rx="8" fill="#0a0a0f" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="360" y="87" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">uomp CLI / GUI</text>

          <rect x="560" y="60" width="120" height="44" rx="8" fill="#0a0a0f" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="620" y="87" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">Auth Service</text>

          <rect x="300" y="170" width="120" height="44" rx="8" fill="#0a0a0f" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="360" y="197" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">Memory Guard</text>

          <rect x="560" y="170" width="120" height="44" rx="8" fill="#0a0a0f" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" />
          <text x="620" y="197" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">Memory Store</text>

          <line x1="130" y1="115" x2="300" y2="90" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead-en)" />
          <text x="210" y="95" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="10" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">1. uom.json</text>

          <line x1="420" y1="82" x2="560" y2="82" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead-en)" />
          <text x="490" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="10" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">2. authorize</text>

          <line x1="620" y1="104" x2="130" y2="145" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead-en)" />
          <text x="380" y="155" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="10" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">3. Capability Token</text>

          <line x1="130" y1="155" x2="300" y2="192" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead-en)" />
          <text x="210" y="185" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="10" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">4. HTTP + Token</text>

          <line x1="420" y1="192" x2="560" y2="192" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowhead-en)" />
          <text x="490" y="215" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="10" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">5. filter by scope</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Discover an Agent</strong>: Browse an Agent marketplace (e.g., an ERC8004-based registry).</li>
        <li><strong>Review the Manifest</strong>: The Agent declares its identity and requested memory scope in <code>uom.json</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Connect & Authorize</strong>: You confirm the scope, and the Auth Service issues a short-lived Capability Token.</li>
        <li><strong>Access Data</strong>: The Agent accesses Memory Guard within the authorized scope.</li>
        <li><strong>Disconnect</strong>: The session ends or you revoke it, and the token becomes invalid immediately.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Who Is UOMP For?</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">👤</div>
          <h3>Users</h3>
          <p>Regain control over personal data and know exactly which Agents accessed what.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🤖</div>
          <h3>Agent Developers</h3>
          <p>Access user-authorized data through a standard protocol without building your own store.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🔬</div>
          <h3>Protocol Researchers</h3>
          <p>Help design an open, decentralized authorization standard for Agent memory.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Explore UOMP</h2>
      <p>Read the protocol draft, check out the reference implementation, or join the GitHub discussion to build a user-sovereign Agent memory authorization standard together.</p>
      <div class="cta">
        <a href={`${baseUrl}en/spec/`} class="btn btn-primary">Read the Spec</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/0xaicrypto/uomp-core" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-secondary">View Implementation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
